<p>I made a view <strong>Lista</strong> that adds a form in partial view with ajax to <code>&lt;tr id="myRow"&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;</code> in Lista.</p>  <p>In partial view I have:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;%@ Control Language="C#" Inherits="System.Web.Mvc.ViewUserControl&lt;BeekersInfo.Schemes.GrowerPickingList&gt;" %&gt;  &lt;% using (Html.BeginForm("OnSave", "DailyPickingList"))    {%&gt;     &lt;%: Html.ValidationSummary(true)%&gt;         &lt;td&gt;             &lt;input type="submit" value="Save" /&gt;         &lt;/td&gt;         &lt;td&gt;             &lt;%: Html.TextBoxFor(model =&gt; model.Remark, new { style = "width:110px; font-size:100%;" })%&gt;             &lt;%: Html.ValidationMessageFor(model =&gt; model.Remark)%&gt;         &lt;/td&gt; &lt;% } %&gt; </code></pre>  <p>End when I debug the function OnSave in dailypickinglist isn't called.</p>  <p>In html file it is shown:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;tr id="tr1"&gt;&lt;form action="/DailyPickingList/OnSave" method="post"&gt;&lt;/form&gt; &lt;td&gt;     &lt;input type="submit" value="Save"&gt; &lt;/td&gt; &lt;td&gt;     &lt;input id="Remark" name="Remark" style="width:110px; font-size:100%;" type="text" value="Testing app"&gt; &lt;/td&gt; </code></pre>  <p></p>  <pre><code>[HttpPost] public PartialViewResult OnSave()//string rowID, string palletID) {    return PartialView("SingleRowPalletID"); } </code></pre>  <p>Maybe it is about that <code>&lt;form&gt;&lt;/form&gt;</code> doesn't catch the <code>&lt;input type="submit" /&gt;</code></p>